data.text:
I've Enjoyed a Week Away!

Well, a week away from tumblr. In real life I've recently returned home from my summer performance contract, and have been getting back into the swing of my regular 9-5 jobs and other things. But I've also been hard at work rewriting Chapter Two! I've already got ten posts written out, and more to go, and I'm super excited to see how it evolves from the original! There will be a lot of drama at least, you can count on that!

But on top of all that, I've decided to take a stab at something I've wanted to try for a while, and that's streaming! I watch people play games all the time on youtube, and I figured....why couldn't I try it myself!

I'd love to see some of you over there if it's something you're interested in doing! You can find me on both YouTube and Twitch at AlideThornolie, and I'd be happy if you'd give me a follow! I'm planning to stream within the next hour and if you wanted to come hang out I'd love that!

For those waiting for 1 October? Have no fear! You're in for a real treat!

Les Anciennes Falaises: 31 Mai 1850, 19:20

Mademoiselle Eleanor: What are you doing?

Monseigneur Oliver: What does it look like?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: You cannot be serious!

Monseigneur Oliver: I've never been more serious about anything in my entire life.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: But what about la mascarade-

Monseigneur Oliver: Eleanor-

Mademoiselle Eleanor: The letters-

Monseigneur Oliver: Eleanor...forget about it. Forget about all of it.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: ...

Monseigneur Oliver: Eleanor Mireille Alexandrine Valery. I have loved you for as long as I can possibly remember. In love with the woman who averts her eyes if you stare at her for a moment too long, the woman who shyly turns away when she's caught staring herself. The woman whose hair flies free when she's out riding, whose shimmering gaze attempts to hide deep cavernous secrets when she hesitates to speak her mind. You are a woman who loves with every fibre of your being. A woman entranced by sunsents, the fall of rain...and above all...

Monseigneur Oliver: You are the woman who loves me...loves me in a way no one else can. During these past few weeks I have had to endure endless conversations with women who could not see the part of me that was not le Monseigneur...and I could never share my life with someone who could not see beyond my title.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Oliver...

Monseigneur Oliver: Tomorrow I am to stand before a room full of people, announcing my engagement to all of Thornolia. To make a speech as a future Monsieur le Roi. But I kneel before you tonight as a man, and not as le Monseigneur. Away from prying eyes and whispers. To lay my heart and soul before you, and only you. Je t'aime, Eleanor. Until the last breath leaves my body I will never love another...so do me the greatest honour of becoming my wife....s'il vous plaît.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: ....Oui.

Monseigneur Oliver: Quoi?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: [Smiles] Oui....Oui, Mon Prince. Je t'aime.

Monseigneur Oliver: Vraiment?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Vraiment.

Les Anciennes Falaises: 31 Mai 1850, 19:15

Monseigneur Oliver: Eleanor!

Monseigneur Oliver: Ma dulcinée, what's the matter?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Oliver...how did you find me?

Monseigneur Oliver: Ernest.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: But how did you know where-

Monseigneur Oliver: I know you, Eleanor. Now tell me what's happened.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: I cannot do this...

Monseigneur Oliver: Do what? What has happened?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: We...we cannot be together. There can no longer be anything between us. Not...not anymore.

Monseigneur Oliver: Arrêtez. You're speaking nonsense.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Oliver, s'il vous plaît. I cannot bear the fear....you have to let me go.

Monseigneur Oliver: Ma chérie, I refuse to listen to this. Are you being threatened? Have you received another letter? Dites-moi. I will do whatever is necessary to stop them. Anything except let you walk away from us. I would never be able to bear it. Tell me what has happened....s'il vous plaît...

Mademoiselle Eleanor: I...I received another letter.

Monseigneur Oliver: And its contents? What did it say?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: [Cries] Non...Oliver, s'il vous plaît. I cannot-

Monseigneur Oliver: You must, ma chérie.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: They said I chose poorly...that...that my days are numbered...

Monseigneur Oliver: And you have no idea who sent this?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Non. I found the letter sitting on my dressing table...Oliver, who would write such a thing?

Monseigneur Oliver: Je ne sais pas, but you can be certain the moment I find out they will be punished.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Non, don't you see? Our only solution is to give them what they-

Monseigneur Oliver: Absolutely not.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Oliver-

Monseigneur Oliver: Non. I will not endure any more discussions of separating. I'd rather die than walk away from you.

Mademoiselle Eleanor: But what if whoever is behind these letters is not just threatening me? What if they were to come for you? You cannot expect me to simply allow something to happen to you.

Monseigneur Oliver: Eleanor, what have I always said to you?

Mademoiselle Eleanor: You cannot always protect me, Oliver. Nor I you.

Monseigneur Oliver: And perhaps you're right, but that does not negate the fact I would travel to the ends of the earth to try. Je t'aime, Eleanor. Every breath in my body, every thought I possess...it's all of you. So to imagine, even for a moment, living a life without you...it's incomprehensible...[Kneels]

Mademoiselle Eleanor: Oliver...Oliver?

Only Three Posts Left of Chapter One!

It’s hard to believe after all the ups and downs I’ve experienced since I lost my blog back in 2021, I’m finally at the end of the rewrite of chapter one! What was originally only around 50 posts was rewritten and updated to 160! It’s definitely a labour of love and I’m so happy with how the rewrite has been going!

There will be a new post later today, one tomorrow, and the final one on Friday! After that, I will take the next two months to finish rewriting and staging Chapter Two, with its return to come on 1 October!

Anyone who remembers the original, and for those first time readers, Chapter Two takes place all in the course of one day: 1 June 1850, which is not only Oliver’s birthday, but the date of the Masquerade. Lots happens in one day, and I’m so looking forward to sharing with you not just the bits I’d written before, but also new scenes (and a new character 👀….)! I can’t wait to show you everything I have planned!

But for now, please enjoy the final three posts of Chapter One, and take the time to both read and catch up over the next two months in preparation for the next chapter! You’re not gonna want to miss out!

The Chaos is Soon to Begin….

Manoir de Thornwood: 31 Mai 1850, 18:30

Madame Adelaide: He's impossible. Does he really expect us to sit here and do nothing?

Monseigneur Oliver: None of what he's doing makes any sense. But you can bet I'll uncover what is going on here. He cannot expect us to live our lives shrouded in darkness from within his precious little guilded cage.

Madame Adelaide: Not to mention-

Steward: Pardonnez-moi, vos atesses royales.

Madame Adelaide: Goodness!

Monseigneur Oliver: Who is this?

Footmen: Laurent, Monseigneur. I apologise for my appearance, but I am one of the footmen at Chateau de Clèrisseau.

Monseigneur Oliver: Clèrisseau?

Footmen: Oui, Monseigneur. I have a letter of utmost urgency for you. I was instructed to place it into your hands directly.

Steward: I apologise for the interruption, but he was most insistent.

Monseigneur Oliver: It's quite alright. Merci, Laurent.

Madame Adelaide: Make sure Laurent here is given some food and drink before he leaves. Something warm, Messier. With the storm it must not have been a thouroughly plesant journey.

Steward: Of course, Madame. Right this way, Monsieur.

Footmen: Merci, vos altesses royales.

Madame Adelaide: What is it? Is it from Eleanor?

Monseigneur Oliver: Non...it's from Ernest.

Madame Adelaide: Ernest?

Monseigneur Oliver: ...Eleanor's taken off.

Madame Adelaide: Quoi? Why? Where did she go?

Monseigneur Oliver: He doesn't know. He only says she was in distress and in quite a state when she took off.

Madame Adelaide: You have to go find her, Oliver. She'll catch her death if she's out too long in this storm!

Monseigneur Oliver: What about-

Madame Adelaide: I'll cover for you. Aller. Just go find her.

Monseigneur Oliver: Merci, Addy.

Madame Adelaide: Just go!
